  "directionsTitle": "Method",
  "directionGroups": [
   {
    "title": null,
    "steps": [
     "Slice the onion into rings and fry in a pot until glassy.<img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/KOOL-035.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt title=\"KOOL-035\">",
     "Cut the meat into cubes and fry until brown together with the onion.<img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/KOOL-042.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt title=\"KOOL-042\">",
     "Cut your potatoes into cubes and add to the meat.<img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/KOOL-045.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt title=\"KOOL-045\">",
     "Finely slice your cabbage and add to the meat.<img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/KOOL-063.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt title=\"KOOL-063\">",
     "Mix together all the rest of the ingredients and add to your meat.",
     "Now put the lid on and let it cook gently  – at least slowly for 90 minutes.<br><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1500\" height=\"1125\" src=\"/media/uploads/2017/10/KOOL-069.jpg\" class=\"direction-step-image\" alt title=\"KOOL-069\">",
     "If you feel the sauce is too runny you can thicken it with Bisto. This stays soul food that tastes just as good the next day."
